15396,Linkity,[],['Word Game'],"Every player starts with 7 cards and each card has a letter. The first player plays a card and announces a word that starts with that letter. Then any player can throw down another card as long as they can announce a word that starts with the letter on their card AND that has some relationship to the card previously played.<br/><br/>Poor associations can be challenged and players vote on the acceptance of the explanation. If the explanation is valid, the challenger takes two cards from the discard pile. If it is voted down, the player that played the card picks up two cards.<br/><br/>Once a player is out of cards, the round ends and each player scores the number of cards remaining in their hand. After three rounds, the player with the lowest score wins.<br/><br/>WHAT THEY'LL LEARN: Vocabulary, Quick Thinking, Word Association<br/><br/>",2004,,,
15397,Sound Alikes A game using homonyms,[],"['Card Game', 'Word Game']","The object of the game is to score the most points. Roll the dice to determine the order of play. The highest roll gives the clues first. There are 2 groups of words: one group has 2 homonyms and one group has three homonyms. The group of 2 is worth 10 points and the group of 3 is worth 20 points. Keep score on the points provided.<br/><br/>The player going first chooses a card with 2 homonyms and reads the clue to the player with the second highest roll of the dice. That player has 10 seconds to say the homonym. If he/she cannot, the next player in order has a chance etc. When that card is done the player with the second highest roll reads the clues to the other players. After all have read a clue with 2 words, a card with 3 is read.<br/><br/>The game ends when time expires (agreed upon) or when all the cards are read. The player with the most points wins.<br/><br/>",2004,,,
15398,Fight Dice,"['Action Points', 'Area Movement', 'Dice Rolling']","['Dice', 'Fighting', 'Science Fiction']","Fight Dice is a freely downloadable PDF-based dice based combat system adapted for action figure battles.  Players allocate (six-sided) dice from a pool for each action figure to allow for movement and/or combat.  Combat consists of sets of dice rolled for attack and defense (as allocated,) defense dice that are equal or higher cancel attack dice, the number of remaining attack dice are removed from the defender's dice pool.  Movement is one inch for each die allocated to movement.  Advanced rules allow for enhanced movement/range mechanics, foreign objects, grappling, etc.<br/><br/>The game guidelines state that a standard human gets 8 dice, a martial artist 20 and a Gundam Fighter gets 36.  Players are encouraged to use their imagination to assign values to action figures.<br/><br/>",2002,,,
