16419,The Enchanting Village,"['Roll / Spin and Move', 'Set Collection']",['Dice'],"This game's subtitle, 'A playful introduction to the people and cultures of Africa' is perhaps overstating things. This game consists of rolling and moving around the board collecting things that are supposed to tell us about Africa (coconuts, tree, necklace, fish, mask, drum, hut...). Each player has a board with pictures of 9 of the 16 objects to be collected and rolls the die to move around the board and fill up her or his board. The only further 'complication' is that there are some arrow squares on the board, some pointing clockwise, some anticlockwise. It would appear that landing on these squares can change the direction the player is going in. Landing on any other square gets one of the objects, if its one the player needs.<br/><br/>This is intended as a child's first game. My copy is missing the rulebook, but it isn't hard to surmise the basic rules.<br/><br/>",1989,,,
16420,Catch Phrase Junior,[],"[""Children's Game"", 'Party Game']","Same as Catch Phrase but words or phrases that appear on the readout are familiar to adults and well as children. Anyone who can read can play.  Players sit in a circle and divide teams into every other person. One person is selected as the starting player or &quot;Clue Giver.&quot; After reading the &quot;target word&quot; on the game's display, the clue giver yells out associated words, hints, sounds until his/her team guesses the target word. As soon as this happens the player presses the Next button and passes the game device to next player who must now give clues to his/her team.  All the while the timer is ticking down. Beep...Beep...Beep..Beep..Beep.Beep.BeepBeepBeep! <br/>If your team is not in possession of the game device when the buzzer goes off and you score! First team to 7 wins!!<br/><br/>",2002,,,
16421,The Miss America Pageant,['Roll / Spin and Move'],['Movies / TV / Radio theme'],"This game recreates The Miss America Pageant with players competing in the Swimsuit, Talent, Personality and Evening Gown competitions. The game uses a spinner shaped to look like a television camera. On your turn, you spin the spinner and advance the number of spaces indicated. If you land on a competition space, you draw a card that tells you what score you received for that event. When you have cards from all the competitions, you place your contestant piece on one of the 3 Semi-Final spaces and start a new contestant. It is possible for a player to have 0, 1, 2 or 3 contestants in the Semi-Final judging. When all 3 Semi-Finalist spaces are filled, the player with the highest point score moves her contestant to a Finalist space. A new round is then played and so on until all 5 Finalist spaces are filled around the base of the camera. The spinner is then spun and the contestant in front of the camera pointer is named 4th runner up and removed. This process is repeated eliminating 1 contestant at a time. The remaining contestant is named Miss America, and the player who controls her wins the game.<br/><br/>",1974,,,
