16556,Penny Candy,['Memory'],"[""Children's Game"", 'Memory']","This is a simple matching game with a candy store theme. To begin, the 36 candy cards (gumdrops, candy corn, lollipops etc.) are randomly inserted into slots on the board. On your turn you spin the spinner and get either a result of &quot;1 cent&quot; or &quot;2 cents&quot;. If you spin a 1, you pull 1 card from a slot. If you don't have a card in front of you, place it face up in front of you. If you do have a candy card in front of you, but this card doesn't match it, put it back (and remember what it is for later). If you do have a candy card in front of you and this card matches it, set both cards aside and draw again. A spin of 2 allows you to draw 2 cards on your turn. The player with the most matches when all the candy cards have been drawn from the board wins.<br/><br/>",1986,,,
