16805,Road to Berlin: Platoon Level Combat in World War II – A Panzer Grenadier Game,['Hexagon Grid'],"['Wargame', 'World War II']","A game in the &quot;Panzer Grenader&quot; series, this covers the late-war armored battles with Germany on the defensive.<br/><br/>From the AP website:<br/>				<br/>				<br/>					Road to Berlin is loaded with heavy gear, featuring 825 pieces.<br/><br/>The Germans get Royal Tiger tanks for the first time in the Panzer Grenadier series, plus giant lumbering vehicles like the Hunting Tiger with its 128mm gun and the Hunting Panther. There are the fast Hetzer tank destroyers, too. Road to Berlin has both regular army and Waffen SS pieces, including SS cavalry. There are also pieces for the German home-defense militia called out in the last days of the Thousand-Year Reich.<br/><br/>The Red Army of Workers and Peasants is also loaded with powerful weapons: The JS-1 and JS-2 heavy tanks lead the way, but there are also all sorts of vehicles not seen before by Panzer Grenadier fans: T-34/85, T-70 and KV-85 tanks; SU-76, SU-85, SU-100, SU-122, SU-152 and JSU-152 assault guns. There&rsquo;s also 122mm artillery for the first time, and Ba64 armored cars.<br/><br/>Returning to the Panzer Grenadier system are the Soviet Guards, the elite of the Soviet armed forces. They bring the modern weapons of 1944 and 1945 plus rocket launchers and a full array of ground forces. We first debuted these in Heroes of the Soviet Union, which will be retired when the last copies are sold, but this is a much fuller treatment.<br/><br/>Just as Eastern Front includes the Armata Romana, so does Road to Berlin bring the Royal Honvedseg, Hungary&rsquo;s army. The Hungarians have excellent cavalry and a number of Hungarian-made armored vehicles that are, well, less than excellent: Turan and Toldi tanks and Nimrod and Zrinyi assault guns.<br/><br/>As for playing surface, Road to Berlin features eight of the semi-rigid mapboards of the type found in Airborne and Eastern Front. These are new to players of the series, with art by Terry Moore Strickland.<br/><br/>And as will be true for all games in the series, there are plentiful replay opportunity: 75 scenarios drawn from the battles of 1944 and 1945 on the Eastern Front. <br/>				<br/>				<br/>					This game is part of the Panzer Grenadier series<br/><br/>Expanded by:<br/><br/>    Arctic Front: Finland's War, 1939-1944 – A Panzer Grenadier Scenario Book: Deluxe Edition<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: Blue Division<br/>    Campaigns & Commanders: War in the East, 1939-1945 – A Panzer Grenadier Campaign Book<br/>    Edelweiss: A Panzer Grenadier Scenario Book<br/>    First Axis: Slovakia at War 1939-1945 – A Panzer Grenadier Scenario Book<br/>    Fronte Russo: A Panzer Grenadier Expansion Book<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: Iron Curtain<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: Iron Wolves – Lithuania's Army<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: March on Leningrad<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: North Wind<br/>    Red Warriors<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: Siege of Leningrad<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: South Africa's War<br/>    Panzer Grenadier: War on the Equator<br/>    White Eagles: A Panzer Grenadier Supplement Book<br/><br/><br/>",2005,,,
