16807,Swipe,['Dice Rolling'],['Dice'],"Swipe is a specialty dice-rolling game. Each of the game's ten dice are marked with five different symbols - a red circle, a blue square, a red circle with an inscribed &quot;S&quot; (for Swipe), a blue square with an inscribed &quot;S&quot; and a black square with an inscribed &quot;X&quot;. There are two red circles on each die.<br/><br/>Players (from 2-6) begin with two dice, and two red chips. Remaining dice and chips (of which there are a total of 50) are placed in the center of playing space. Youngest player rolls dice and acts according to symbols, as follows:<br/><br/><br/>    Blue Square - take a die from center. <br/>    Blue Square with inscribed &quot;S&quot; - take (Swipe) a die from any opposing player. <br/>    Red circle - take a chip from center. <br/>    Red circle with inscribed &quot;S&quot; - take a chip from any opposing player. <br/>    Black square with inscribed &quot;X&quot; - lose a die to center<br/><br/><br/>A special rule is the Super Swipe, where all dice rolled end up as a Black X.  In this case, the player gets to take a die from all opposing players and then takes another turn.<br/><br/>Winner is the player with most red chips when center pile of chips is completely depleted.<br/><br/>",2004,,,
