16995,La Grande Corsa,"['Modular Board', 'Roll / Spin and Move']","['Card Game', 'Movies / TV / Radio theme', 'Racing']","A sort of &quot;game of goose&quot; (or &quot;snake and ladders&quot;). <br/>It has no board, but a deck of cards (square tiles), shuffled and put face down to form the track at the beginning of the game: the first player landing on each card reveals it and follows the given instructions (e.g. &quot;move one space backward&quot;, &quot;nothing happens&quot;, &quot;reach the last player&quot;, etc.); these effects are valid for the rest of the game. <br/>Each player has a pawn (shaped as a car) starting at one end of the track. The goal of the game is to bring your pawn to the other end of the track. <br/>To play, you simply roll a six-sided die, move your pawn exactly that number of spaces forward and execute the instructions on the card you've reached. After that, it's the turn of the next player.<br/>Thus there's no decision to take in the whole game: simply roll the die and hope.<br/>The track made with cards acts as a &quot;modular board&quot; (it is different in every game).<br/>The game was licensed by the Walt Disney Company and so the cards show some of the famous Disney characters.<br/><br/>",0,,,
