17289,Stellar Journey,[],['Educational'],"&quot;Far beyond the Milky Way, undisturbed for billions of years, lies a vast, cold cloud of molecular hydrogen, helium, and dust. Penetrating shock waves from a distant supernova or a close encounter with a passing star disrupts the cloud, setting its gases and dust in motion. Forcibly separated into numerous fragments, the gigantic cloud is transformed into an immense stellar nursery from which hundreds of bright, shining stars will emerge.<br/><br/>To play STELLAR JOURNEY: The Game, each player gathers &quot;mass&quot; to form three stars, plus &quot;time&quot; for each to evolve through all stages from beginning to end. The first player to complete the life cycles of all three - ending in a white dwarf, a neutron star, and a black hole - wins! Whether new to astronomy or a veteran stargazer, whether competing with family, friends, or classmates, whether young or old, STELLAR JOURNEY: The Game is certain to provide hours of wholesome fun, learning, and adventure!<br/><br/>STELLAR JOURNEY: The Game <br/>Simulates star birth from nursery to end stages <br/>Four levels of difficulty permitting players to compete at their own level <br/>No regressive plays - lose your next turn, etc. <br/>GAME CONTENTS:<br/>Game board; game pieces; sixty colorful cards presenting a total of 300 questions at four levels of difficulty; and a booklet containing the rules of play, record charts, game objectives, match to the National Science Education Standards, image credits, and glossary.&quot;<br/><br/>Stellar Journey: The game was developed in cooperation with NASA'S Chandra X-ray Center and the Harvard-Smithsonian Center for Astrophysics, and The Wright Center for Innovative Science Education, Tufts University.<br/><br/>",0,,,
17290,People & Places in The Book,['Roll / Spin and Move'],"['Religious', 'Trivia']","A Bible trivia game a bit different from the usual Trivial Pursuit style.<br/><br/>There are six questions to each answer, in decreasing difficulty (6 being the most difficult).  In this game, players progress along a game track.  Movement forward (or backward for incorrect answers) is determined by the level of difficulty you are attempting.<br/><br/>There are several types of square, which determine who may answer the question.  A solo square means only the person whose marker is on the square may answer.  A Free-For-All square means all players have the opportunity to answer.  A Proxy square means the active player chooses another player to answer for them; the active player advances on the correct answer, but the proxy goes back if they answer incorrectly.  A Blitz square allows everyone to answer as the active player reads the clues from most difficult to easiest.  As soon as someone answers correctly, they and the active player move ahead the number of squares matching the level of clue that was the question was answered on.<br/><br/>Each players turn finishes after one move.<br/><br/>There are also Providence cards, which usually result in either going forward or back a number of squares.<br/><br/>First to reach the finish square wins.<br/><br/>",1986,,,
17291,"Can't Cook, Won't Cook",['Roll / Spin and Move'],"['Educational', 'Humor', 'Movies / TV / Radio theme', 'Party Game', 'Trivia']","Based on the BBC Television Series of the same name, Can't Cook, Won't Cook is a lighthearted family game for 2 to 6 players Ages 10 and up<br/><br/>From the box:<br/><br/>&quot;They say &quot;If you can't stand the heat then get out of the kitchen!&quot; the same is true of this exciting, fast paced family action packed board game.<br/>It's a race to get your ingredients for a perfect meal traveling up and down the board a few times to collect them. sounds simple...well it would hardly be based on the hit TV show, if it were that easy!!<br/>Firstly, it's against the clock, then it's against another player, then you have to answer some &quot;Can't Cook&quot; or &quot;Won't Cook&quot; questions, oh and did we mention you could be rolling the pastry, tossing the pancake, chopping the herbs, stirring the pans....&quot;<br/><br/>The objective is to move around the board in order to collect points. Points are collected as you collect ingredient tokens. The game ends when the first player has collected all 5 ingredients. Movement is determined by dice roll with each player taking turns to have one minute (a sand timer is provided) to move and accomplish as much as they can.<br/><br/>The spaces on the board dictate the activities to be undertaken on them. These include:<br/>- collecting an ingredient, <br/>- pausing for a cup of tea (rolling until you get a 2),<br/>- answering questions (cookery related - involving choosing your answer from a choice of four) or <br/>- performing an action - stir the pan, roll the pastry, chop the herbs or toss the pancake (the equipment for which is all included with the game)<br/><br/>",1995,,,
17292,Limbo,[],"['Action / Dexterity', 'Party Game']","Limbo - How Low Can You Go?<br/><br/>Components:<br/>5 Limbo Blocks (wooden blocks (5cm x 5cm x 13cm)<br/>1 Limbo Bar (wooden block (0.5cm x 5cm x 13cm) with Velcro pad<br/>1 Limbo-low-nose (with Velcro pad)<br/><br/>The five limbo blocks are stacked on top of each other on the floor with the limbo bar on the top.  Players take it in turns to wear the &quot;Limbo-low-nose&quot; and bend over an pick up the limbo bar with their nose.  This must be achieved with only the feet in contact with the floor.  Each player has three attempts - players who cannot do this, or touch the floor with any part of their body other than their feet are eliminated.<br/><br/>Once everyone has succeeded or been eliminated the bar is lowered by removing one of the limbo blocks so that the limbo bar is now resting on four blocks.  Players now attempt at this height.<br/><br/>Play continues in this way, gradually reducing the height of the bar until either only one player is left or until at least two players have successfully picked up the bar from the floor.  If this happens all five blocks are placed under the limbo bar again, and the exercise repeated, but this time players are only allowed to stand on one foot!<br/><br/>",1995,,,
