17669,Covered With Glory,['Simulation'],"['Miniatures', 'Napoleonic', 'Wargame']","From the Designer:<br/><br/>Covered With Glory is designed to reflect the tactics of the Napoleonic period at the level where those tactics had the most impact - the company and battalion. The unique movement and morale systems make the obstacles faced by officers of the period all too evident as players try to coordinate the movements of the units within their brigade or division. This is a fast paced, easy to learn, easy to play games system in which exciting and challenging battles can be played with as few as three or four battalions on each side or as much as a division.<br/><br/>This is not a game of high strategy. It is a game of tactics at a level too long ignored or simply not understood. It is a game about the common soldier and how he was led, maneuvered and deployed as he covered himself with glory.<br/><br/>",1993,,,
17670,Whistchievous,['Trick-taking'],['Card Game'],"WICKED WHIST is a board game which adds another dimension to the classic card game - Whist.<br/><br/>The object of the game is to graduate from one corner of the playing board to the eye at the center.  This is achieved by playing Whist and, after each hand, moving clockwise around the board - one square for each trick made.  The first player to reach the center (having made exactly the right number of tricks) is the winner.<br/><br/>There are two ways of achieving this:<br/><br/>1.  By completing full circuits of the board and by moving from one level to the next at selected points.<br/><br/>OR<br/><br/>2.  By means of special squares which send you from outer to inner circuits (or vice versa) in a manner similar to Snakes and Ladders.<br/><br/>The layout of the board forces players to consider in advance how many tricks they require to win so as to land on an advantage square, or avoid a forfeit square.  At the same time they must also consider what they need to do to force their opponents into minimizing the tricks they win, or forcing tricks on them so that they land on a forfeit square.<br/><br/>",1989,,,
