17677,Flying Fortress,['Hidden Victory Points'],"['Aviation / Flight', 'Wargame', 'World War II']","Two of the &quot;Test Series&quot; games released by Poultron Press, the forerunner of SPI. Flying Fortress was Test Series Game 2 and Flying Fortress II was Test Series Game 10. The games covered the Allied strategic bombing in Europe during World War II.<br/><br/>The games covered both US and British bombing efforts. Planes include B-17s, B-24s, Lancasters, and Halifaxes. (B-29s are in the optional rules.)<br/><br/>The games were reportedly the first to use hidden victory conditions (the &quot;nidden victory points&quot; mechanism is the closest available equivalent). Flying Fortress II may have been the first game with double-sided counters (the back used for step reduction).<br/><br/>Each turn in the game was a separate &quot;tactical mission&quot; game representing a month of real time. These turns were linked together to make a campaign. The mission game rules were divided into basic, standard, and advanced levels.<br/><br/>",1969,,,
