18423,Tortellini Football,"['Point to Point Movement', 'Simultaneous Action Selection']","['Print & Play', 'Sports']","A football game for two players played on a checkerboard.<br/><br/>Each player has three pieces to represent his team. There is a ball. A goal is scored when a team successfully lands a piece carrying the ball in its opponent's end zone. The game ends when one team has successfully scored five goals.<br/><br/>Each turn, pieces of the team with the ball -- the offensive team -- can either move or pass the ball. The defensive team's pieces can only move in an attempt to take possession of the ball. If the defensive team takes the ball, it becomes the offensive team.<br/><br/>Moves and passes are declared in secret and then simultaneously revealed. Pieces move simultaneously.<br/><br/>Official Rules: <a target='_blank' href=""http://boardgames.about.com/library/games/on/bl-simul-tortellinifootball.htm"" rel=""nofollow noreferrer noopener"">http://boardgames.about.com/library/games/on/bl-simul-tortel...</a><br/><br/>",2003,,,
18424,Frames,"['Enclosure', 'Paper-and-Pencil', 'Simultaneous Action Selection']",['Abstract Strategy'],"Frames is played by two players on a Go board with its pieces, and a few neutral pieces. It can also be played with pencil and paper, because once placed, the pieces can not be moved.  The moves are simultaneous. In each turn, both players place one of their pieces in an intersection of the board.  If the intersection chosen by both players is the same, a neutral piece is placed instead. Otherwise, both pieces just placed define a rectangle of intersections on the board.  The player who has more pieces inside that rectangle (the pieces in the borders of the rectangle are not counted) earns a point.  The first player to earn a total of ten points is the winner.<br/><br/>Online Play<br/><br/><br/>    Super Duper Games<br/><br/><br/>",2003,,,
