19130,Antipod,[],['Abstract Strategy'],"Antipod is a connection game with unequal goals played on the two halves of a sphere.<br/><br/>Antipod is played on two equally sized hex boards, typically with six cells per side. The board is set up with a black piece in the center of each half, forming Black&rsquo;s antipodal goals, and white pieces placed at the six corners of each board, forming White&rsquo;s handicap pieces.<br/><br/>Black wins by forming a chain of black pieces between the antipodal goals of each board half. White wins by preventing a Black win. This amounts to completing a cycle of white pieces around at least one of Black&rsquo;s antipodal goals. Exactly one player must win.<br/><br/>",2003,,,
