19162,Heximoes,['Tile Placement'],['Abstract Strategy'],"&quot;the six-sided strategy game&quot;<br/><br/>Heximoes includes 132 six-sided cardboard tiles. Each side has a number of dots, between one and six. As in dominoes, you make matches, but must make sure all sides line up: sixes against sixes, fives against fives, etc. In the main game, each player takes six tiles from the box. If you can not make a play, you must draw an additional tile. Play continues until one player has placed all of his tiles on the table, or until no other players can make a play. Variants, including a solitaire, are also included.<br/><br/>",2004,,,
