19257,Le Truc,"['Betting and Bluffing', 'Trick-taking']","['Bluffing', 'Card Game']","Le Truc is a 15th century card game from France and Spain. Sid Sackson included it in A Gamut of Games.<br/><br/>Le Truc is a betting/bluffing/trick-taking game for two players or two teams of two players. It is played in rounds of 12 points and the first side to take two rounds wins. For each hand, players are dealt three cards from a French 32-card deck. A hand is initially worth one point, but the active player may propose a raise in stakes before answering each trick. A hand is won by taking the majority of tricks or by making the opponent(s) fold to a raise. Only ranks of cards are important in Le Truc, not suits. If two cards of the same rank are played in a trick it is &quot;spoiled&quot; and not counted for either side. The first trick of a hand is particularly important, because it acts as a tiebreaker when both sides win an equal number of tricks.<br/><br/>There is a Brazilian variant know as Truco that also includes a card value to have higher in-game value than others. This value changes at each trick by drawing a card.<br/><br/>",0,,,
19258,Diner Chess,[],"['Deduction', 'Print & Play']","A game of late-night deduction and coffee for two or more players.<br/><br/>Object: To figure out the secret rules that govern how the other players move pieces on their turn.<br/><br/>You Need:<br/><br/>* An area with diverse items that you can group in general categories. A table with four place settings at your local late-night diner should do nicely.<br/>    * Paper and pencil for each player.<br/><br/>Each player makes up a rule and writes it down. The player's rules dictates how he moves pieces when it's his turn. On each player's turn, the player moves a piece in accordance with his secret rule and then asks a yes/no question to another player. Players can also guess other players' rules for points.<br/><br/>The game ends when all rules but one have been guessed. If your rule remains unguessed, then you lose 1 point. The player with the most points wins.<br/><br/>",2003,,,
