19558,Spellbinding,['Roll / Spin and Move'],"['Dice', 'Word Game']","Spellbinding is a word game where the objective is to successfully identify a scrambled word while in the center space on the board and controlling the dice. The board consists of three concentric circles, divided into spaces, and a large center space.<br/><br/>When a player is in control of the dice, the player to his right is the SPELLBINDER. The SPELLBINDER is the game's arbiter. His duties are as follows: he selects a card from the deck; he scrambles the letters of a word on the card, which is indicated by the board or the second die; he presents that scrambled word; he determines who is the first to correctly identify the word (and whether a tie has taken place). The other players have one minute to identify the word. The first to identify the word gains (or keeps) control of the dice.<br/>If no player correctly identifies the word, play continues to the left.<br/><br/>This process continues until a winner is determined.<br/><br/>",1989,,,
